VARIABLE DCAFEPLUS
;
VARIABLE DANBET
VARIABLE DANDICE
;
NUMBER 3176
NAME Saloon
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
This good-sized barroom is filled with the sounds of laughter and clinking
glasses produced by the many patrons who occupy its round wooden tables and
lean against the impressive, stained oak bar. The wall behind the bar is
mostly occupied by a large, silvered mirror which seems to double the size
of the room. A portrait hangs just between the mirror and a narrow wooden
stairway. Also at the back of the room, on the east and west walls, a door
and an archway face each other along the length of the bar, each made from
the same type of fine, polished oak as the bar, the stairway and the tables.
*DESCRIPTION_END
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
ITEM 0 773 ADJ1=355 ADJ2=1064 VAL2=205
EXTEND 0 that occupy only half of their doorway
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
The doors are made from frames of curving wood, filled out with unpainted
slats which rest at an angle, letting sunlight fall to the floor near them
in narrow bands but blocking the view of a casual passerby in the street.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 1 81 ADJ1=210 VAL2=3180
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 1
You guess that they just might lead up to the second floor...
*DESCRIPTION_END

ITEM 2 1127 ADJ1=771
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 2
The dart board is a circle of red, green and black wedges, numbered along
the edges. You can never quite recall the rules of the game, of course, but
you can simply RECALL BOARD for them.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFVERB RECALL 2
  ECHO PLAYER Look on the board for darts; if there are none, thump the board to get
  ECHO PLAYER the bartender's attention and he will replace them. Take a dart and USE
  ECHO PLAYER it to get a grip, then CAST it to cast it at the board. You may adjust
  ECHO PLAYER your aim a little up or down by pulling and waving the dart, and if you
  ECHO PLAYER gaze at the board you can assess your aim at the moment. You may ask the
  ECHO PLAYER bartender for your score by pointing at the board. He'll understand.
ENDIF
PUT 2 13
PUT 2 13
PUT 2 13
PUT 2 13
PUT 2 13
IFPREVERB POINT 2
  IFVAR FLAG3 > 0
    CLEARVERB
    STRCVT 0 FLAG3
    ECHO ALL The bartender says, "%N, you have %0 points."
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB THUMP 2
  ECHO ALL The bartender runs around and sticks a new round of five darts onto the dart board.
  REMOVEITEM 2
  NEWITEM 2 1127 ADJ1=771
  NEWPUT 2 13
  NEWPUT 2 13
  NEWPUT 2 13
  NEWPUT 2 13
  NEWPUT 2 13
ENDIF
IFPREVERB USE -1
  IFVAR ARCHNUM = 13
    CLEARVERB
    ECHO PLAYER You get a good grip on %a.
    ECHO OTHERS %N gets a good grip on %a.
    EQUAL FLAG1 100
    RANDOM FLAG2 1 100 -50
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB GAZE 2
  IFVAR FLAG1 < 100
    ECHO PLAYER You don't have a dart ready to throw, so you don't think you'll hit much.
  ENDIF
  IFVAR FLAG1 = 100
    IFVAR FLAG2 <= 0
      ECHO PLAYER You don't think you'll hit inside the outer circle. Perhaps a little more aiming.
    ENDIF
    IFVAR FLAG2 > 0
      IFVAR FLAG2 < 25
        ECHO PLAYER You think you'll hit inside the outer circle, for up to twenty points. You're not sure, though.
      ENDIF
      IFVAR FLAG2 > 24
        ECHO PLAYER You're sure that you will hit within the outer circle, perhaps even the bullseye.
      ENDIF
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB PULL -1
  IFVAR ARCHNUM = 13
    IFVAR FLAG1 = 100
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You pull back slightly, going for a tad more altitude.
      ECHO OTHERS %N pulls back on %a slightly, looking for a better throw.
      IFVAR FLAG2 < 0
        RANDOM DUMMY1 1 20 8
        ADD FLAG2 DUMMY1
      ENDIF
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB WAVE -1
  IFVAR ARCHNUM = 13
    IFVAR FLAG1 = 100
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You waggle the dart a little to one side.
      ECHO OTHERS %N waggles %a a little to one side.
      IFVAR FLAG2 > 0
        IFVAR FLAG2 < 25
          RANDOM DUMMY1 1 20 8
          ADD FLAG2 DUMMY1
        ENDIF
      ENDIF
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB CAST -1
  IFVAR ARCHNUM = 13
    IFVAR FLAG1 = 100
      CLEARVERB
      ECHO PLAYER You cast the dart at the board.
      ECHO OTHERS %N hurls %a at the dart board!
      DIV FLAG2 2
      SKILLCHECK 3 FLAG2 DUMMY1
      IFVAR DUMMY1 < 0
        ECHO ALL The dart misses entirely, thunking into the wall!
        REMOVEITEM -1
        NEWPUT 8 13
      ENDIF
      IFVAR DUMMY1 >= 0
        IFVAR DUMMY1 < 10
          ECHO ALL The dart thunks into the outer edge of the board, for five points.
          REMOVEITEM -1
          NEWPUT 2 13
          ADD FLAG3 5
        ENDIF
      ENDIF
      IFVAR DUMMY1 > 9
        IFVAR DUMMY1 < 25
          RANDOM DUMMY2 1 10 20
          STRCVT 0 DUMMY2
          ECHO ALL The dart thunks into the inner circle, for %0 points!
          REMOVEITEM -1
          NEWPUT 2 13
          ADD FLAG3 DUMMY2
        ENDIF
      ENDIF
      IFVAR DUMMY1 > 24
        ECHO ALL Bullseye! 50 points!
        REMOVEITEM -1
        NEWPUT 2 13
        ADD FLAG3 50
      ENDIF
      EQUAL FLAG1 0
      EQUAL FLAG2 0
    ENDIF
  ENDIF
ENDIF
;
EXIT E 3178
EXIT W 3177
ITEM 4 91 ADJ1=447
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 4
This table, like all of them in this room, is made from fine oak planks cut
and fitted together into a great, thick circle. It is supported at the center
by a massive wooden post which splits into four curving, carved lion paws.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 5 86
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 5
Every chair in the saloon is high-backed and made from good white pine, its
four legs ending in the same carved lion's paws that grace the large round
tables as well. Each has a breaking wave carved into its back.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 6 1342 ADJ1=308 ADJ2=447
EXTEND 6 polished to a high lustre
PUT 6 1279 ADJ1=32
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 6
The swirling grain of the good solid oak which was used to construct this bar
has been brought to the surface to a stunning degree through the application
of good, dark stain and many hours of polishing.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 8 204
EXTEND 8 on the wall above the bar
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 8
The sign is a list of the drinks available here.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM READ 8
Brew and wine       Price
-------------       -----
Ale                 16 Pennies
Champagne            2 Crowns
Emerald Wine        25 Shillings
Grog                 7 Pennies
Honey Mead           3 Shillings

Hard stuff          Price
----------          -----
Effervescent Frappe 2 Crowns
Shartan Toddy       3 Crowns
Dragonslayer Tonic  3 Crowns
Faydish Fizz        2 Crowns

We have rolls! Chicken, beef and vegetable, 12 Shillings each!
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 7 420
