NUMBER 3177
NAME Saloon, casino
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
A smoky haze fills the air of this room, softening the edges of your vision
in a not unpleasant way. Thick, plush carpeting covers the floor and felt
and velvet cover the tables and panels on the walls, all combining to reduce
the level of noise in the same way. A mustachioed man with a red armband
rattles dice in his hands at a table here at the north of the room. A
carved oaken archway leads out to the saloon, where louder pleasures
await the careful customer.
*DESCRIPTION_END
INDOOR_FLOOR
FIXED_LIGHT
ITEM 0 60 ADJ1=447 VAL2=3176
IFENTRY
  IFVAR PLRSINROOM = 1
    EQUAL DANBET 0
    EQUAL DANDICE 0
  ENDIF
ENDIF
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
The archway is fashioned from fine, dark-stained oak wood, carved to resemble
two stacks of dice (threes and fours facing outward) supporting a segmented
roulette wheel. Beyond it you see the saloon proper.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 3 91 ADJ1=152
EXTEND 3 on the north side of the room
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 3
The attendant, a man with a thick black mustache, stands at one end of
this long, skinny table with his stacks of dice which have been, you hear,
inspected by agents of the King himself to insure that they have not been
tampered with. The other end of the table is boxed in by three low, soft
barriers designed to trap the dice when he throws them. A sign on the side
of the table indicates that the minimum bet is one gold crown, as well as
explaining the rules of the game for the uninitiated.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 2 204 ADJ1=355
EXTEND 2 on the side of the craps table
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 2
Amazingly enough, the sign is covered with writing.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM READ 2
.                      .
.         Rules of the Game:             .
. Drop your money (in gold only, please) and point to it in order      .
. to place your bet. Then, get the dice and roll them down the table.  .
. A first roll of 2, 3, or 12 is an automatic loss. A first roll of 7  .
. is an automatic win, and you will recieve back twice as much as you  .
. bet. A first roll of 11 is a partial win, good for a 5 crown return  .
. on your original investment. Any other roll becomes your point.      .
. Thereafter, you will roll until you hit your point again, thereby    .
. winning the game, or until you roll a 7, thereby losing it.          .
. No side bets will be supported by the casino at this time due to     .
. circumstances beyond our control. The casino reserves the right to   .
. refuse any bet beyond a certain amount, dependent on circumstances   .
. at that time. We apologize for any inconvenience.                    .
.                                                                      .
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFPREVERB GO 3
	CLEARVERB
	IFVAR FLAG2 > 199
		ECHO PLAYER You're already there, silly.
	ENDIF
	IFVAR FLAG2 < 200
		ECHO PLAYER You walk over to the craps table and take your place in the crowd.
		ECHO OTHERS %N walks over to the craps table.
		EQUAL FLAG2 200
	ENDIF
ENDIF
;
;
; CLEARER
IFPREVERB EXIT -1
	IFVAR FLAG2 > 200
		EQUAL DANBET 0
		EQUAL DANDICE 0
	ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB GO 0
	IFVAR FLAG2 > 200
		EQUAL DANBET 0
		EQUAL DANDICE 0
	ENDIF
ENDIF
;
;    CRAPS
IFPREVERB STOMP -1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO ALL With a rattling sound the craps table attendant clears the board.
  EQUAL DANBET 0
  EQUAL DANDICE 0
ENDIF
